description:
Madara of the Akatsuki joins the fray on the battlefield. His powerful attacks, and a secret plan, take their toll on the Allied Shinobi Forces. Naruto and Bee rush to help their friends, but the leader of the Cloud Village will do anything to stop Naruto from risking his life—even if he has to fight Naruto to do it!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 535: Iruka's Impact
  • Chapter 536: Battle...!!
  • Chapter 537: Toward Nightfall...!!
  • Chapter 538: Cross-Examination
  • Chapter 539: Blood Night...!!
  • Chapter 540: Madara's Scheme!!
  • Chapter 541: Raikage vs. Naruto?!
  • Chapter 542: The Secret Origin of the Ultimate Tag Team!!
  • Chapter 543: Truer Words
  • Chapter 544: Two Suns!!
name: Battle

description: Natsume meets a kindhearted yokai who has found a ruined letter he desperately needs to read. There is another yokai who has power over paper who might be able to help him. But this yokai’s name is sealed in the Book of Friends… Will it be willing to help the grandson of the woman who bound it?!
name: Vol. 12

description: Luffy and the princess of Fish-Man Island escape the castle and head to the mysterious Forest of the Sea. Meanwhile, the kingdom is under attack by dark forces. What is the source of the hatred between humans and the merfolk?!
name: Otohime and Tiger

description: The yearly culture festival is coming up fast, and it’s a great chance for Midorigaoka Academy to shine. But disappearing students and rising tensions between the academy and nearby Kiyama High could turn the festival into a full-on disaster! Can a pack of delinquents save the day and the school?
name: Vol. 9

description: "I have goals to achieve. Dreams to make come true." Plus, a new CRIMSON CORSAIR backup feature from writer LEN WEIN and artist JOHN HIGGINS!
name: I Met a Traveler...!; The Curse of the Crimson Corsair, The Devil in the Deep: Part Five

description:
It’s modern warfare versus prehistoric horror in “The War That Time Forgot”!

The Unknown Soldier and his newfound super powers head to Pakistan in search of chemical weapons…and retribution!
name: The War that Time Forgot; The Unknown Soldier, Chapter Three

description:
BARON WINTERS is trapped in the past while his NIGHT FORCE agents fight alone!

ZOE is captured!

A terrifying ritual centers on a presidential candidate
name: Book One: 250 Minutes, Chapter 5: The Dormants

description:
Continuing the re-presentation of the entire saga of Mike Grell's classic character, Jon Sable, Freelance. This seventh collection delves deeper in creator Mike Grell's First Comics run, featuring issues 34-39, where Sable encounters white slavers, travels back to Africa, and more.

Collects Jon Sable, Freelance #34-39.
name: Vol. 7

description: Can the Enterfowl crew convince a race of moles to evacuate before the Hawkons arrive? Read, "None Are So (Duck) Blind"! Also, crew member Ducky Mitchell gains god-like powers in "Where No Duck Has Waddled Before!"

Don't get confused. Eerie made a mistake in numbering issues in Volume 5 of this series. Note that this issue was labeled "Volume 5, Number 2" in the indicia even though the April 1981 issue was also labeled "Volume 5, Number 2". This magazine, the August 1981 issue, is actually the third magazine published as part of Volume 5.
How and why the war ended.
name: A Dog's Life

description: Stinz reveals what happened to end The War.
name: A Marvelous Resistance

description: "The End Of The War" comes to the valley.
name: Playthings

description: 5th Century Britain. Rome's Legions have gone leaving chaos. Deposed King Vortigern flees to Wales, where he meets an ageless, inhuman youth sired by a demon. His name is Merlin and he foretells the coming of the true king, Uther, head of the Pendragon dynasty, who with vengeance in his heart and battle in his blood, will reunite the British Isles and drive the invaders back into a sea turned red with blood; and how, when victory is in his grasp, his lust for another's wife will send it slipping from his hand, bringing chaos and anarchy, but also bringing into the world a son who will be the greatest hero of all time - King Arthur.

person_credits.name: Jack T. Chick
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: This volume collects four issues previously uncollected in any other Final Crisis-related collection. It includes Final Crisis #1: Director's Cut, which contains an uncoloured version of the first issue, the original script and a page-by-page commentary from writer Grant Morrison and artist J.G. Jones, Final Crisis: Secret Files, which tells the origins of Libra, Final Crisis: Requiem, where the heroes of the DC Universe mourn the loss of their friend J'onn J'onzz and try to carry out his final wishes, and Final Crisis: Resist, where Mr. Terrific, Snapper Carr and Checkmate try to fight back against Darkseid and the Anti-Life Equation.
name: Final Crisis Companion

description:
Charlie Brown, Snoopy, Linus, Lucy and the rest of the Peanuts gang's return to comic books is all here in one heart-warming volume. Collecting the first four issues, this trade brings you the perfect balance, with brand-new adventures and classic Sunday strips from Schulz himself. This is one book that will delight old and young fans alike, from the most devoted fans to readers picking up their first comic book.

Collects the first Peanuts mini-series from KaBoom.
name: Volume One

description:
White’s beloved Pokémon and star performer Gigi abandons her for another Trainer! Will White ever overcome her fears and learn to battle with her Pokémon?

And will Black take on the challenge of Nimbasa City’s Battle Subway?!

Plus, meet Cubchoo, Bouffalant, Accelgor, Mienshao, Sigilyph, Deerling, and Tirtouga.

Chapter Titles

  • Adventure 25: Gigi's Choice
  • Adventure 26: Unraveling Mysteries
  • Adventure 27: A New Perspective
  • Adventure 28: Growing Pains
name: Vol. 8

description:
Meet the puppy with a tail like a cinnamon roll!

Cinnamoroll is no ordinary pup. He loves freshly baked cinnamon rolls and uses his long ears to fly high into the sky! With his friends Chiffon, Mocha, Espresso, Cappuccino and little Milk, he’s always on the lookout for a new adventure.

The pups set up a specialty crepe shop for the animals in the forest. But the squirrels throw out everything but the nuts, the raccoons wash away the best part, and the chickens want their crepes made with worms. Gyaah!
name: Vol. 4

description: A video recording shows a dark vision of the future, where many of Ageha’s friends are ruthlessly killed. To escape the danger posed by W.I.S.E, Ageha, Sakurako and the others must battle their way to freedom. But even if they escape, can they really fight fate and alter that treacherous future?
name: Visions

description: A ghost at the skating rink, a restless spirit from the Taisho era, and Rinne’s deadbeat damashigami dad going into the ramen business?! Rinne’s got a real outbreak of strange problems and ghosts to deal with. And if that’s not enough, Rinne gets sucked into a spat between Ageha and her Black Cat by Contract, Oboro!
name: Vol. 9

description:
Compared to Fairy Tale HQ, what is the goal of Fairy Tale’s branch office?

a. the same

b. the opposite

c. better parking spots
name: Vol. 9

description: Kyoko’s dreams are finally coming true! She’s landed a spot in Sho’s new video, and revenge is in sight! But vengeance isn’t as easy as she thought, and her rage starts to get in the way of her acting. When her performance catches the attention of some important people, Kyoko finds herself working with the terrifying Ren Tsuruga! Can she make it work, or will her growing fame be her downfall?!
name: Volume 7-9

description: Ren’s new roles are dredging up old memories best left buried, and he’s having trouble dealing with the emotional turmoil. But the President was right when he claimed Kyoko was Ren’s good luck charm. Will her strange but good-natured ways be enough to keep him from his own darkness?
name: Vol. 28

description:
Cross Academy is attended by two groups of students: the Day Class and the Night Class. At twilight, when the students of the Day Class return to their dorm, they cross paths with the Night Class on their way to school. Yuki Cross and Zero Kiryu are the Guardians of the school, protecting the Day Class from the Academy's dark secret: the Night Class is full of vampires!

The Vampire Hunter Society has imprisoned Aido in order to interrogate him about Kaname’s connection to Sara Shirabuki. Meanwhile, Yuki wants a fresh start with Kaname, but circumstances arise that may force them apart.

Contents

  • Sixty-Fourth Night: Proposition at the End of a Thousand Nights
  • Sixty-Fifth Night: The Unscrupulous Princess
  • Sixty-Sixth Night: Starting Over Again
  • Sixty-Seventh Night: The Blade That Severs All
  • Sixty-Eighth Night: Why?
  • Vampires Covered in Blood Are Prohibited from Entering This Page!!
name: Vol. 14

description: Before Bloom became part of the Winx Club, she was living a normal teenager's life. All that changed one day when she discovered that she’s actually a fairy! Now Bloom’s life is anything but ordinary as she uses her magic to fight wicked villains!
name: Bloom's Discovery

description: To hone her fairy powers, Bloom enrolls at Alfea, a school for fairies in the world of Magix. But when wayward witches known as The Trix threaten to ruin a party at Alfea, it’s up to Bloom to save the day with some quick thinking!
name: Secrets of Alfea

description: Ever since they first met, Amon has been preparing Gwen for the coming of Xitalu, the Great Devourer from beyond space and time. But no one warned the rest of the people in town! And now that Xitalu is almost here, threatening to consume every living soul on Earth, will Gwen be able to do what’s necessary to save the world?
name: The End, Part 3

description: A spree killer terrorizes New Orleans days before Hurricane Katrina makes landfall. Detective Curt Delatte just buried his only daughter, and he''s in no condition to work. But when the bodies pile up, he masks his grief and joins the hunt through the bowels of the Big Easy. It won''t be long until his city - and his evidence - gets washed away!
name: TPB

volume.name: Sweets: A New Orleans Crime Story

description: This edition collects the complete run of THE SWORD in an oversized hardcover and slipcase format. Experience the epic story about a young woman who finds a mysteriously powerful sword that allows her to seek revenge on the three elemental gods who brutally murdered her family. Contains all covers, including rare versions from extra printings.
name: HC

description: 100,000 years before the time of John Carter! Barsoom is a dying world: its once mighty oceans are receding and its atmosphere grows more tenuous by the day. The Orovars, who have dominated for a million years, are on the verge of extinction at the hands of the Green Hordes and the emerging Red Martians. Two Orovars - a Scientist and a General - race against time to save their people before Mars plunges into barbarism! This trade paperback collects the Warlord of Mars: Fall of Barsoom 5-issue series into one volume, with a cover gallery and bonus material.
name: TPB

volume.name: Warlord of Mars: Fall of Barsoom
Wizard Special: The Begining of the Valiant Era

description: Asterix and nuclear, a spurious book (original in German: "Asterix und Atomkraftwerk") published in Castilian in 1981 by the environmental group Brisa. It is edited with vignettes of other books with the text completely altered. The end result was a new story whose aim was to publicize the dangers of nuclear power plants. The aim was to "spread it, pass it, photocopy it, play it on strips of newspapers, magazines ... show it to parents or children" in the words of the authors. At the end of the book are pictures of real people who fought at the time to prevent the installation of energy production centers.
name: Asterix y las nucleares
Como Obelix se cayo en la marmita del druida cuando era pequeño
